      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "STUBBORN EMMELIE (7) raced on the pace and stuck on gamely but found one better on debut over this distance at Wyong last start. In good hands and with that run under her belt she looks ready to open her account. THE MAGNET (8) has not been produced since October when she led for the judge on debut over today's trip at Hawkesbury before fading. The winner of two recent trials so she looks to be back in great shape and can give this a shake. GAMP (4) is back after a 195-day spell. Opened last prep with a game second at Newcastle then went on to fill four straight top four finishes before being turned out. Recent Rosehill trial winner who looks ready for another bright return. BRAZEN DIVA (3) registered her sixth minor placing from 11 starts when she led but just failed to hold on over 1200m at Port Macquarie recently. Placed at three of six over 1000m - sure to take some catching. SAMMY THE BULL (2) did enough first-up to suggest he is in for a decent campaign.",
